Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%carton}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Boil the @basmati rice{150%grams}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain and pop back in the pan. Cover.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%grams}. Fry, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Once browned, drain and discard any excess fat from the beef.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the kidney beans, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%carton}, @chipotle paste{20%grams}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}.

Stir and bring to the boil. Simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chipotle chilli.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese.

Enjoy!